	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Washington</placeName> <date>Feb. 1. 1863</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Phila</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
				<p>I feel bound to you as an old friend and<lb/> associate in the garden of <placeName>Israel</placeName> to <sic>anounce</sic><lb/> to you the decease of my father&#45;in&#45;law <persName>Rabbi<lb/> P. M. Heilprin</persName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Hereby I enclose a Necrologue&#44;<lb/> which I wish you may insert in your next<lb/> No of the Occident in the language as<lb/> I composed it and <hi rend="underline">verbally&#8212;</hi>provided it<lb/> would <sic>corrospond</sic> with your intention.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The memory of the that great man deserves<lb/> it&#44; that <placeName>Israel</placeName> should know&#44; who he<lb/> was&#8212;as a century may pass <sic>untill</sic><lb/> another <persName>Heilprin</persName> will be born.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">If you find it more proper&#44; please<lb/> translate it in English&#8212;as I have but<lb/> little capacity for it&#8212;and I request<lb/> you to send me two copies of that<lb/> No by mail.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Should you decline it altogether&#8212;<lb/> please return me the writing.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In every way I remain with<lb/> high regard</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Yours respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">M. I. Franklin</persName></p>
			
